Comment (src/views/dashboard/partials/SuggestionScopeDialog.vue:28):
**[Medium] Label-set selector shows the raw hash, not a human title.** `optionLabel="hash"` (with `display="chip"`) means the selected chips and the collapsed label render the opaque label-set `hash`. The 'Create New Dashboard' evidence picker the maintainer referenced does this right — `EvidenceDashboardForm.vue` uses `optionLabel="title"` and an `#option` slot showing the evidence `title`. The `#option` dropdown slot here already shows the label chips + evidence count, but the *selected* value still collapses to the hash.

Suggestion: show a human-readable Label Set Title for the selected chips, mirroring the evidence picker. Keep `optionValue="hash"` for the payload, but drive the displayed label from a title — `DashboardSuggestionLabelSet` already has `sampleTitles?: string[]` (dashboard-suggestions.ts:18) you could surface (e.g. first sample title, or a formatted-labels summary) via `optionLabel` or a `#chip`/selected slot. Note `sampleTitles` is optional and may be empty — if a stable title is required, consider having the label-sets endpoint return one.
