Comment (src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue:420):
**[Medium] Control options show only the control ID — no title, no profile.** `controlOptions` maps each implemented requirement to `{ label: requirement.controlId, value: requirement.controlId }`, so the picker shows bare IDs like 'AC-2'. The maintainer wants (a) the control **title** alongside the ID and (b) which **profile(s)** each control belongs to. Both need data this computed doesn't currently have:

- **Title:** `ImplementedRequirement` carries only `controlId` (no title); titles live in the catalog. There's an existing resolve pattern to copy — `CreateFormView.vue`'s `getControlSelectList` builds `control.id + ' ' + control.title` from the fetched full catalog. Label these as e.g. `${controlId} — ${controlTitle}`.
- **Profile membership:** not present in the SSP `/full` response. There's a per-SSP profiles endpoint (`/api/oscal/system-security-plans/:id/profiles`, stores/system-security-plans.ts:110) returning `{ uuid, title }` per bound profile, but it does **not** map control→profile. Showing 'which profiles this control belongs to' requires resolving each bound profile's controls (e.g. `/api/oscal/profiles/:id/resolved-with-catalogs`) and matching by controlId, then tagging each option with the profile title(s).

Suggestion: enrich `controlOptions` to include the resolved control title and a profile annotation (group-by-profile in the MultiSelect, or a per-option profile chip). Please scope the extra fetches — title needs a catalog fetch; profile membership needs resolving the bound profiles.
Implementation guidance: In src/views/dashboard/partials/SuggestionScopeDialog.vue, keep the label-set MultiSelect payload keyed by hash with optionValue="hash", but stop using optionLabel="hash" for display. Add a small formatter such as getLabelSetTitle(labelSet: DashboardSuggestionLabelSet) that returns the first non-empty sampleTitles entry when available, otherwise a readable summary of the labelSet.labels values, and only falls back to the hash when no human-readable data exists. Wire this into the selected chip/collapsed display using the PrimeVue MultiSelect selected/chip slot if optionLabel cannot call a formatter directly. Keep the existing dropdown option slot that shows label chips and evidence count, but make selected values show the human title/summary rather than the opaque hash. Handle optional or empty sampleTitles without throwing.
Implementation guidance: In src/views/dashboard/SuggestionsView.vue, enrich controlOptions so the scope picker displays control ID plus catalog title and profile membership instead of bare IDs. Follow the existing catalog-resolution pattern in src/views/dashboard/CreateFormView.vue getControlSelectList: fetch the relevant full catalog data already used elsewhere in the app, build a controlId-to-title map, and format labels like `${controlId} - ${controlTitle}` with a controlId-only fallback while data is loading or missing. For profile membership, use the SSP-bound profiles endpoint from src/stores/system-security-plans.ts for the current sspId, then resolve each bound profile through the existing profile resolved-with-catalogs API/store helper if one exists; build a controlId-to-profileTitles map by matching resolved profile controls to implementedRequirement.controlId. Add the profile titles to each option, either as grouped options by profile if the current MultiSelect supports it cleanly, or as per-option metadata rendered in the option slot/chip. Keep option.value as requirement.controlId so generate payloads remain unchanged. Scope the fetches to the current sspId, guard all async data with empty-map fallbacks, dedupe profile titles, and avoid blocking render if catalog/profile resolution fails.
